cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper discusses a dataset of optical illusions images, which is relevant to computer vision research. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses human perception and tricks that cause misjudgment, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of models trained on the dataset suggests relevance to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper mentions the potential for insights into how human perception achieves feats, which could relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
